            <h2>Introduction to Adverbs, Conjunctions, and Prepositions</h2>
            <p><span class="initial-letter darkorange-text">A</span>dverbs, conjunctions, and prepositions are the small
                but important words that enhance, join, and show the relationship between the nouns, adjectives and verbs in a sentence.
                Unlike nouns, which decline, and verbs, which conjugate, these words do not change based on number or
                case, and they have no gender or strength. For example, examine the below sentence,
                '<em>þa fuglas ond þa oxan beoþ on þæm felda - The birds and the oxen are in the field</em>'.
                The words '<em>ond</em>' and '<em>on</em>' will always be the same, irrespective of the genders, cases,
                or number of the nouns they are modifying.
            </p>
