            <p>An <strong>adverb</strong> is a word that modifies a verb, adjective, clause, or other adverb.</p>
            <p>A <strong>conjunction</strong> is a word which connects words and clauses with each other.</p>
            <p>A <strong>preposition</strong> is a word which shows how a verb relates to a noun or pronoun.</p>
            <p>Starting with adverbs, let’s look at how these relational words are formed, when they are used, and which
                ones have changed in modern usage.</p>
